---
/**
 * §03 protocol — mid-turn capacity shaper fail-open vs backend final-request verdict.
 */
---

<svg
  class="svv-flow"
  viewBox="0 0 868 292"
  xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
  role="presentation"
  focusable="false"
>
  <defs>
    <marker
      id="svv-arrow"
      viewBox="0 0 10 10"
      refX="9"
      refY="5"
      markerWidth="6"
      markerHeight="6"
      orient="auto-start-reverse"
    >
      <path d="M 0 1.5 L 9 5 L 0 8.5 Z" fill="var(--accent)"></path>
    </marker>
  </defs>

  <text class="svv-kicker svv-stage svv-stage--0" x="8" y="20" fill="var(--accent)">
    PROTOCOL · SHAPING ≠ VERDICT · SINGLE FINAL-PAYLOAD OWNER
  </text>
  <line
    class="svv-stage svv-stage--0"
    x1="8"
    y1="34"
    x2="860"
    y2="34"
    stroke="var(--hair)"
    stroke-width="1"
  ></line>

  <!-- Shaper lane -->
  <g class="svv-stage svv-stage--1" transform="translate(8,48)">
    <rect width="420" height="168" rx="1" fill="var(--bg)" stroke="var(--hair)"></rect>
    <rect width="420" height="2" fill="var(--accent)" opacity="0.55"></rect>
    <text class="svv-idx" x="14" y="26" fill="var(--accent)">SHAPER · mid-turn-capacity-compact</text>
    <text class="svv-title" x="14" y="54" fill="var(--ink)">Select safe prefix · build mid_turn</text>
    <text class="svv-mute" x="14" y="82" fill="var(--mute)">skip · fail_open · compacted</text>
    <text class="svv-mute" x="14" y="104" fill="var(--mute)">never straddles tool pair</text>
    <text class="svv-mute" x="14" y="126" fill="var(--mute)">pin steering · no partials</text>
    <text class="svv-line" x="14" y="154" fill="var(--ink)">MUST NOT issue context_budget_exhausted</text>
  </g>

  <path
    class="svv-stage svv-stage--2"
    d="M 440 132 H 468"
    stroke="var(--accent)"
    stroke-width="1.25"
    fill="none"
    marker-end="url(#svv-arrow)"
  ></path>
  <text class="svv-mute svv-stage svv-stage--2" x="430" y="118" fill="var(--accent)">after all hooks</text>

  <!-- Verdict lane -->
  <g class="svv-stage svv-stage--3" transform="translate(476,48)">
    <rect width="384" height="168" rx="1" fill="var(--soft)" stroke="var(--accent)"></rect>
    <rect width="384" height="2" fill="var(--accent)"></rect>
    <text class="svv-idx" x="14" y="26" fill="var(--accent)">VERDICT · backend final request</text>
    <text class="svv-title" x="14" y="54" fill="var(--ink)">Measure outgoing payload</text>
    <text class="svv-mute" x="14" y="82" fill="var(--mute)">messages + tools that go out</text>
    <text class="svv-mute" x="14" y="104" fill="var(--mute)">after prune + shaping</text>
    <text class="svv-mute" x="14" y="126" fill="var(--mute)">refuse non-shrinking fold</text>
    <text class="svv-line" x="14" y="154" fill="var(--ink)">continue OR context_budget_exhausted</text>
  </g>

  <text class="svv-foot svv-stage svv-stage--4" x="8" y="256" fill="var(--mute)">
    Fail-open under the window keeps the raw projection + diagnostic. Only the final-request estimate owner may terminate — and only about the request that really leaves.
  </text>
  <text class="svv-foot svv-stage svv-stage--4" x="8" y="280" fill="var(--mute)">
    Trigger uses last INPUT tokens + signed char delta (credits shrink). Post-fold raw-ledger re-estimate is not the verdict.
  </text>
</svg>

<style>
  .svv-flow {
    font-family: var(--sans);
  }
  .svv-kicker {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 10.5px;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
  }
  .svv-idx {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
  }
  .svv-title {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: 14.5px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: -0.015em;
  }
  .svv-line {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .svv-mute {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  }
  .svv-foot {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: 12.5px;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: no-preference) {
    .svv-stage {
      opacity: 0;
      animation: svv-fade 0.6s cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1) forwards;
    }
    .svv-stage--0 {
      animation-delay: 0.04s;
    }
    .svv-stage--1 {
      animation-delay: 0.14s;
    }
    .svv-stage--2 {
      animation-delay: 0.28s;
    }
    .svv-stage--3 {
      animation-delay: 0.36s;
    }
    .svv-stage--4 {
      animation-delay: 0.5s;
    }
    @keyframes svv-fade {
      from {
        opacity: 0;
      }
      to {
        opacity: 1;
      }
    }
  }
  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    .svv-stage {
      opacity: 1;
      animation: none;
    }
  }
</style>
